  "title": "fix(autocomplete): trigger initial refine in js implementation",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes a discrepancy between JS and React implementations of the Autocomplete widget. In JS, it now triggers an initial search request with the `query` from the target index.\r\n\r\nI also moved the default `hitsPerPage` to the configure of the actual index, the initial refine solving the issue that prompted to set `hitsPerPage` to a higher level.\r\n\r\nFX-3571",
